"It is obvious. And now, you see, I had narrowed the field down considerably. The possession of a
grey garment was a third point which, granting the son's statement to be correct, was a certainty.
We have come now out of mere vagueness to the definite conception of an Australian from Ballarat
with a grey cloak."

"Certainly."

"And one who was at home in the district, for the pool can only be approached by the farm or by the
estate, where strangers could hardly wander."

"Quite so."

"Then comes our expedition of to-day. By an examination of the ground I gained the trifling details
which I gave to that imbecile Lestrade, as to the personality of the criminal."

"But how did you gain them?"